        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 6:28PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Geneva, or 8 miles southeast of Berne, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Berne, Geneva, Westchester, Trinity, New Corydon, Ceylon, and
Bellfountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
